<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en" data-theme="light">

<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Terms & Conditions - FMPG</title>
    <link rel="icon" href="/img/logo.png" type="image/icon type">
    
    <!-- Central Tailwind CSS & Theme Config -->
    <%- include('tailwind-head') %>
</head>

<body class="bg-bg-body text-text-primary min-h-screen flex flex-col transition-colors duration-300">
    <!-- Header -->
    <%- include('header') %>

    <!-- Header Banner -->
    <section class="py-12 bg-gradient-to-b from-primary/5 to-transparent border-b border-border-color/60">
        <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 text-center space-y-2">
            <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold font-heading text-primary">Terms & Conditions</h1>
            <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm md:text-base max-w-xl mx-auto">Please review the official guidelines, tenant liabilities, and operational policies governing the FMPG network.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Main Content Workspace -->
    <main class="flex-grow max-w-5xl mx-auto w-full px-6 py-12 md:py-16">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-12 gap-8 items-start animate-fade-in-up">
            
            <!-- Quick Sidebar Index Navigation -->
            <aside class="md:col-span-4 sticky top-24 bg-bg-card/40 border border-border-color/60 rounded-2xl p-5 space-y-3 hidden md:block">
                <h4 class="text-xs font-bold text-text-secondary uppercase tracking-widest border-b border-border-color pb-2 mb-3">Terms Index</h4>
                <nav class="space-y-2 text-xs font-semibold text-text-secondary">
                    <a href="#intro" class="block hover:text-primary transition-colors">1. Introduction</a>
                    <a href="#agreement" class="block hover:text-primary transition-colors">2. Agreement to Terms</a>
                    <a href="#eligibility" class="block hover:text-primary transition-colors">3. User Eligibility</a>
                    <a href="#bookings" class="block hover:text-primary transition-colors">4. Bookings & Payments</a>
                    <a href="#tenants" class="block hover:text-primary transition-colors">5. Tenant Responsibilities</a>
                    <a href="#owners" class="block hover:text-primary transition-colors">6. Owner Responsibilities</a>
                    <a href="#deposits" class="block hover:text-primary transition-colors">7. Security Deposits</a>
                    <a href="#evictions" class="block hover:text-primary transition-colors">8. Termination & Eviction</a>
                    <a href="#liability" class="block hover:text-primary transition-colors">9. Limitation of Liability</a>
                </nav>
            </aside>

            <!-- Detailed Policy Blocks -->
            <article class="md:col-span-8 glass-panel rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-10 border border-border-color shadow-xl space-y-8 font-body text-sm text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
                
                <!-- Section 1 -->
                <section id="intro" class="space-y-3">
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-extrabold font-heading text-text-primary flex items-center gap-2">
                        <span class="w-1.5 h-6 bg-primary rounded"></span>
                        1. Introduction
                    </h2>
                    <p>This document is an electronic record under the Information Technology Act, 2000, and sets forth the terms and conditions for using the FMPG platform, operated by DTwelve Spaces Private Limited. It applies to all users of the website and mobile applications.</p>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 2 -->
                <section id="agreement" class="space-y-3">
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-extrabold font-heading text-text-primary flex items-center gap-2">
                        <span class="w-1.5 h-6 bg-primary rounded"></span>
                        2. Agreement to Terms
                    </h2>
                    <p>By accessing or using the FMPG platform, you agree to be bound by these terms. If you are a minor (under 18 years), your use must be supervised by a parent or guardian who agrees to these terms. Continued use after any changes to the terms indicates your acceptance of the updated terms.</p>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 3 -->
                <section id="eligibility" class="space-y-3">
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-extrabold font-heading text-text-primary flex items-center gap-2">
                        <span class="w-1.5 h-6 bg-primary rounded"></span>
                        3. User Eligibility & Security
                    </h2>
                    <p>You must be 18 years of age or older to create an account. If you are under 18, you must have parental consent to use the platform. We reserve the right to terminate any account or refuse access if you provide false information or violate applicable laws.</p>
                    <p>You are responsible for keeping your account credentials secure. Any activity under your account is your responsibility. Notify us immediately if you suspect unauthorized use of your account.</p>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 4 -->
                <section id="bookings" class="space-y-3">
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-extrabold font-heading text-text-primary flex items-center gap-2">
                        <span class="w-1.5 h-6 bg-primary rounded"></span>
                        4. Bookings & Payments
                    </h2>
                    <p><strong>Booking Confirmation:</strong> All bookings made through the platform are subject to availability and confirmation by the property owner. Once your booking is confirmed, you will receive a confirmation email with the details of your stay.</p>
                    <p><strong>Payment Terms:</strong> Payment for bookings must be made as per the payment schedule provided during the booking process. Failure to make timely payments may result in cancellation of the booking.</p>
                    <p><strong>Refund Policy:</strong> Refunds, if applicable, will be processed according to our refund policy. Please note that booking fees, service charges, or certain deposits may be non-refundable.</p>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 5 -->
                <section id="tenants" class="space-y-3">
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-extrabold font-heading text-text-primary flex items-center gap-2">
                        <span class="w-1.5 h-6 bg-primary rounded"></span>
                        5. Tenant Responsibilities
                    </h2>
                    <p>Tenants are responsible for maintaining the cleanliness and good condition of their rented space. Any damage to the property caused by the tenant will be the tenant’s responsibility to repair or compensate.</p>
                    <p>Tenants may be responsible for paying for utilities such as electricity, water, and internet, unless otherwise specified in the rental agreement. Tenants must report any maintenance issues to the property owner promptly.</p>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 6 -->
                <section id="owners" class="space-y-3">
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-extrabold font-heading text-text-primary flex items-center gap-2">
                        <span class="w-1.5 h-6 bg-primary rounded"></span>
                        6. Property Owner Responsibilities
                    </h2>
                    <p>Property owners are responsible for providing the amenities and services as advertised in the listing. This includes ensuring that the property is clean, safe, and habitable at the start of the tenancy.</p>
                    <p>Property owners must address any maintenance or repair requests in a timely manner to ensure the comfort and safety of the tenant.</p>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 7 -->
                <section id="deposits" class="space-y-3">
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-extrabold font-heading text-text-primary flex items-center gap-2">
                        <span class="w-1.5 h-6 bg-primary rounded"></span>
                        7. Security Deposits
                    </h2>
                    <p>Some bookings may require a security deposit, which is refundable at the end of the tenancy, subject to the condition of the property and compliance with the terms of the agreement.</p>
                    <p>The property owner may deduct from the security deposit for unpaid rent, damage to the property, or other breaches of the agreement. The remaining balance, if any, will be returned to the tenant within the timeframe specified in the rental agreement.</p>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 8 -->
                <section id="evictions" class="space-y-3">
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-extrabold font-heading text-text-primary flex items-center gap-2">
                        <span class="w-1.5 h-6 bg-primary rounded"></span>
                        8. Termination & Eviction
                    </h2>
                    <p>The rental agreement may be terminated by the property owner if the tenant violates any terms of the agreement, including non-payment of rent, property damage, or illegal activities.</p>
                    <p>In the event of termination, the tenant may be required to vacate the property within a specified period. Failure to vacate may result in legal action to enforce eviction.</p>
                </section>

                <!-- Section 9 -->
                <section id="liability" class="space-y-3">
                    <h2 class="text-xl font-extrabold font-heading text-text-primary flex items-center gap-2">
                        <span class="w-1.5 h-6 bg-primary rounded"></span>
                        9. Limitation of Liability
                    </h2>
                    <p>FMPG will not be liable for any indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from your use of the platform, including loss of profits, data, or reputation.</p>
                    <p>FMPG's maximum liability to any user for any claim arising out of or related to the use of the platform is limited to the amount paid by the user, if any, to FMPG in the 12 months preceding the claim.</p>
                </section>

            </article>

        </div>
    </main>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <%- include('footer') %>
</body>

</html>